# Admin tables — sortable by default

Every admin data table MUST use `components/admin/SortableTable.js` (or `SortableTh` + `useTableSort` for bespoke layouts).

- All column headers clickable; toggle asc/desc on repeat click
- Default sort: sensible primary metric descending (opens, sessions, date, etc.)
- Provide `sortValue` for rendered/formatted cells (dates, badges, percentages)
- Do not ship plain `<table>` with static `<th>` for row data in admin pages

Reference: `pages/academy/admin/emails.js` (members table), `pages/academy/admin/engagement.js` (Top Engaged Members).
